links.title: Likelihood And Consequences Of A Tesla Credit Downgrade
links.description: When Tesla (NASDAQ: TSLA) issued $1.8 billion of junk bonds in August, it sought and received ratings on the bonds from both Moody's and Standard & Poor's, the two largest credit rating agencies. The ratings of the bonds were: B3, with a stable outlook by Moody's (a newly assigned rating); and B-, with a negative outlook, by Standard & Poor's (a reaffirmation of a previously assigned rating).

links.title: Tesla hit by class-action lawsuit claiming racial discrimination
links.description: (Reuters) - U.S. automaker Tesla Inc on Monday was hit with a class-action lawsuit claiming its California production plant is a "hotbed for racist behavior." The lawsuit filed in California state court in Oakland is at least the third filed this year by black workers who say they were addressed using racial slurs and that the company ignored their complaints.
